#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.55"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.55:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.55:0.2"
msgid "6. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "6. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.55:0.3"
msgid "55. Paṭhamasamajīvīsutta"
msgstr "55. Equality (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an4.55:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
#. VAR: susumāragire → suṃsumāragire (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: bhesakaḷāvane → bhesakalāvane (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.55:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile "
"Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood."

msgctxt "an4.55:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"nakulapituno gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte "
"āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of the householder Nakula’s father, where he sat on the seat "
"spread out."

msgctxt "an4.55:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho nakulapitā ca gahapati nakulamātā ca gahapatānī yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nakulapitā gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Nakula’s father and the housewife Nakula’s mother went "
"up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Nakula’s father said to "
"the Buddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.55:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato me, bhante, nakulamātā gahapatānī daharasseva daharā ānītā, "
"nābhijānāmi nakulamātaraṃ gahapatāniṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, ever since we were both young, and Nakula’s mother was given to me in "
"marriage, I can’t recall betraying her even in thought, still less in deed."

msgctxt "an4.55:2.2"
msgid ""
"Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ "
"abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti."
msgstr "We want to see each other in both this life and the next.”"

msgctxt "an4.55:2.3"
msgid "Nakulamātāpi kho gahapatānī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Nakula’s mother said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an4.55:2.4"
msgid ""
"“yatohaṃ, bhante, nakulapituno gahapatissa daharasseva daharā ānītā, "
"nābhijānāmi nakulapitaraṃ gahapatiṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, ever since we were both young, and I was given in marriage to Nakula’s "
"father, I can’t recall betraying him even in thought, still less in deed."

msgctxt "an4.55:2.5"
msgid ""
"Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ "
"abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti."
msgstr "We want to see each other in both this life and the next.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.62"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: ubhova → ubho ca (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: passantīti → passissantīti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.55:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Ākaṅkheyyuñce, gahapatayo, ubho jānipatayo diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ "
"passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passituṃ ubhova assu samasaddhā "
"samasīlā samacāgā samapaññā, te diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passanti "
"abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passantīti."
msgstr ""
"“Householders, if wife and husband want to see each other in both this life "
"and the next, they should be equals in faith, ethical conduct, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.1"
msgid "Ubho saddhā vadaññū ca,"
msgstr "When both are faithful and kind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.2"
msgid "saññatā dhammajīvino;"
msgstr "restrained, living properly,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.3"
msgid "Te honti jānipatayo,"
msgstr "then wife and husband"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.4"
msgid "aññamaññaṃ piyaṃvadā."
msgstr "say nice things to each other."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.1"
msgid "Atthāsaṃ pacurā honti,"
msgstr "They get all the things they need,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.2"
msgid "phāsukaṃ upajāyati;"
msgstr "so they live at ease."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.3"
msgid "Amittā dummanā honti,"
msgstr "Their enemies are downhearted,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.4"
msgid "ubhinnaṃ samasīlinaṃ."
msgstr "when both are equal in ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.1"
msgid "Idha dhammaṃ caritvāna,"
msgstr "Having practiced the teaching here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.2"
msgid "samasīlabbatā ubho;"
msgstr "both equal in precepts and observances,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.3"
msgid "Nandino devalokasmiṃ,"
msgstr "they delight in the heavenly realm,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.4"
msgid "modanti kāmakāmino”ti."
msgstr "enjoying all the pleasures they desire.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.55:6.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
